    "A New and Concise Bible Dictionary": "Son of Shemaiah and prince at the court of Jehoiakim. Jer. 36: 12,\n4. It is twice mentioned with Lystra, and is placed on the maps to the east of that city. It has recently been identified with Ambarrarasi, west of Eregli. Descry, To. To search, to spy out. Judges 1:\n4. Elead. [El'ead] Son of Zabad, a descendant of Ephraim. 1 Chr. 7:\n4. It is this weapon that will be beaten into pruning hooks. Isa. 2: 4; Micah 4: 3. b. kidon, a smaller kind of lance, or javelin. Joshua 8: 18, 26; Job 41: 29; Jer. 6: 23. c. tselatsal, harpoon. Job 41: 7. d. qayin, lance, 2 Sam. 21: 16. e. romach, spear used by heavy-armed troops, the iron head of a spear. Judges 5: 8, etc. The pruning hooks are to be beaten into spears in the time of God's judgements. Joel 3:",
    "Dr. Peter S. Ruckman": "This is the \u201csea of glass,\u201d the \u201cdeep.\u201d It is that body of water above the firmament of which we read, \u201cThe face of the deep is frozen\u201d [v_Job_38_30] (Job 38:30). It is the \u201csea\u201d referred to in Job 41:31\u2013\n4. His rewards (1 Cor. 3:13\u201315). [v_Luk_19_15]\n4. Chalcedony\u2014A white translucent stone which symbolizes Levi. (It is also sometimes called the \u201conyx\u201d stone, and is found in Iceland and the New Hebrides Islands.)",
